# Excalidraw — Cursor Rules (legacy format)
# Generated from .cursor/rules/*.mdc

# ─── ALWAYS APPLY ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## Protected Files
# NEVER modify without explicit approval:
# - packages/excalidraw/scene/renderer.ts   (render pipeline)
# - packages/excalidraw/data/restore.ts     (file format compat)
# - packages/excalidraw/actions/manager.ts  (action system)
# - packages/excalidraw/types.ts            (core types)
# Changes require: full dependency review + full test suite + manual QA.

## Memory Bank
# Keep docs/memory/ up to date after every meaningful change.
# Required files: projectbrief.md, productContext.md, systemPatterns.md,
#                 techContext.md, activeContext.md, progress.md
# - After any code change   → update activeContext.md and progress.md
# - After architecture decisions → update systemPatterns.md
# - After dependency/tooling changes → update techContext.md
# - After scope changes → update projectbrief.md and productContext.md

# ─── ARCHITECTURE (packages/excalidraw/**) ────────────────────────────────────

## State Management
# - Use actionManager.dispatch() for all state updates — NOT Redux/Zustand/MobX
# - State type is AppState (packages/excalidraw/types.ts)

## Rendering
# - Canvas 2D only — do NOT use react-konva, fabric.js, pixi.js, or React DOM for drawing
# - Render pipeline: Scene → renderScene() → canvas context

## Dependencies
# - No new npm packages without explicit approval
# - Check packages/utils/ before adding external helpers

# ─── CODE CONVENTIONS (packages/**) ──────────────────────────────────────────

## Components
# - Functional components + hooks ONLY (no class components)
# - Props interface named {ComponentName}Props
# - Named exports only — NO default exports
# - Colocated tests: ComponentName.test.tsx

## TypeScript
# - Strict mode — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
# - Prefer `type` over `interface` for simple types
# - Use `import type { X } from "..."` for type-only imports

## Files
# - kebab-case for utility files: element-utils.ts
# - PascalCase for component files: LayerUI.tsx

# ─── SECURITY ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# - Never use dangerouslySetInnerHTML — use React's safe rendering
# - No eval(), new Function(), or dynamic code execution
# - No hardcoded secrets, tokens, or API keys in source
# - Sanitize all user-supplied input before rendering or processing
# - All shared room data must use end-to-end encryption
# - Never log or expose encryption keys or room IDs
# - Use URL constructor for URL parsing — never string concatenation
# - No new packages parsing SVG/HTML/binary without security review

# ─── MODULE RULES ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

## excalidraw-app/
# - App-level concerns only (routing, persistence, collaboration)
# - Do not duplicate logic from packages/excalidraw — import it
# - Firebase and Socket.io are confined to this package

## packages/common/
# - Shared utilities only — no UI, no canvas, no element logic
# - Must NOT import from other @excalidraw/* packages (no circular imports)

## packages/element/
# - Element types are immutable — never mutate, always return new objects
# - Use mutateElement() for controlled mutations within the package
# - No rendering logic here — rendering belongs in packages/excalidraw

## packages/excalidraw/
# - Public API surface is index.tsx — do not expose internals
# - Component props must be documented with JSDoc
# - Must NOT import from excalidraw-app/ (dependency flows downward only)

## packages/math/
# - Pure functions only — no side effects, no external imports
# - Always use GlobalPoint or LocalPoint from types.ts — never plain { x, y }
# - Every function must have unit tests

## packages/utils/
# - General-purpose helpers — keep functions small and focused
# - Prefer pure functions; avoid stateful utilities